column1: UNICEF, WHO, World Bank Group Joint Malnutrition Estimates, May 2022 Edition.                  Overweight numbers affected (millions) 2000-2020.

Overweight refers to a child who is too heavy for his or her height. This form of malnutrition results from expending too few calories for the amount consumed from food and drinks and increases the risk of noncommunicable diseases later in life.
Overweight (moderate and severe): Number (millions) of children aged 0-59 months who are above two standard deviations from median weight-for-height of the WHO Child Growth Standards.
Oceania excluding Australia and New Zealand
Oceania excluding Australia and New Zealand
1. Consecutive low population coverage; interpret with caution.

2. The estimates for the year 2020 do not account for the full impact of COVID-19.  Household survey data on child height, weight and age were not collected in 2020 due to physical distancing policies. One of the covariates used in the country model takes the impact of COVID-19 partially into account.
